  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Building our Future: Towards Improving Campesino Families&#x2019; Livelihood from the Sierra Madre of Chiapas.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Problems such as dependence in coffee cultivation, migration, loss of food sovereignty, governmental reliance, the lack of food, and loss of solidarity and cooperation are affecting the communities of la Sierra Madre de Chiapas. In this project, agroecological activities will be implemented as an alternate to coffee production. Heifer will provide 2,149 chickens and turkeys, 114 pigs, 85 rabbits, 70 sheep, 24 beehives, 13 horses, 4 fish modules, 205 pounds of vegetable seeds, 1,903 fruit trees and the components for mushrooms production. In a period of five years, 549 families &#x2014; &#xAC;183 originals and 366 by passing on the gift &#x2014; from 12 communities will participate. The families will increase their food, and their income will be increase by selling surplus production, which will strengthen their family livelihood.</narrative>
  </description>
